---
layout: base.njk
title: Templates
nav: templates
permalink: /templates/
---
<div class="ds-eyebrow">Starting points</div>
<h1 class="ds-title">Templates</h1>
<p class="ds-lede">The reusable page scaffolds <em>are</em> the golden page layouts — each one ships a proven desktop layout <strong>and</strong> its responsive mobile counterpart from a single file (the breakpoints live in <code>responsive.css</code>). Rather than invent new scaffolds, start from one of these: copy the golden file, keep the chrome and breakpoints, and swap in your content. Four archetypes cover the product — Home, List, Detail, and Form.</p>

{% for t in templates %}
<h2 class="ds-section">{{ t.name }} <span class="ds-arch">{{ t.archetype }}</span></h2>
<p class="ds-meta-line">{{ t.purpose }}</p>
<div class="ds-tpl">
  <div class="ds-tpl__desktop">
    <div class="ds-tpl__label">Desktop</div>
    <div class="ds-tpl__frame"><iframe src="/examples/pages/{{ t.file }}" title="{{ t.name }} desktop" loading="lazy"></iframe></div>
  </div>
  <figure class="ds-tpl__phone">
    <div class="ds-tpl__label">Responsive (mobile)</div>
    <div class="ds-tpl__screen"><iframe src="/examples/pages/{{ t.file }}" title="{{ t.name }} mobile" loading="lazy"></iframe></div>
  </figure>
</div>
<div class="ds-meta-line">Reuse: {{ t.reuse }}</div>
<div class="ds-meta-line"><a href="/examples/pages/{{ t.file }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open full page ↗</a> · source: <code>package/examples/{{ t.file }}</code></div>
{% endfor %}

<style>
  .ds-arch { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-purple-light, #a18aff);
             border: 1px solid var(--color-purple-tag-border, #3a3170); border-radius: 999px; padding: 2px 10px; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 8px; }
  /* Desktop preview gets the full column width so it renders the real desktop chrome
     (a flex-shrunk iframe under 600px would fall below the mobile breakpoint). The
     phone frame sits beside/below it and shows the true responsive view. */
  .ds-tpl { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: flex-start; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 14px 0 8px; }
  .ds-tpl__desktop { flex: 1 1 640px; min-width: 320px; }
  .ds-tpl__label { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted, #b3a6c8); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .ds-tpl__frame {
    width: 100%; height: 500px; border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-purple-card-border, #2d2850);
    background: var(--color-bg-primary, #140d2c); box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  }
  /* Full column width keeps the iframe above the 600px mobile breakpoint, so the real
     desktop chrome (side-nav + top bar) renders — at full size, not a scaled thumbnail. */
  .ds-tpl__frame iframe { width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0; display: block; }
  .ds-tpl__phone { margin: 0; flex: 0 0 auto; }
  .ds-tpl__screen {
    box-sizing: content-box; width: 300px; height: 620px;
    border-radius: 26px; overflow: hidden; border: 7px solid #241f3d;
    background: #140d2c; box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.45);
  }
  .ds-tpl__screen iframe { width: 390px; height: 806px; border: 0; transform: scale(0.7692); transform-origin: top left; display: block; }
  @media (max-width: 1180px) { .ds-tpl__desktop { flex-basis: 100%; } }
</style>
